title: Lyndon B Johnson National Historical Park: Insects, Spiders, Centipedes, Millipedes
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     Nature     Animals     Insects, Spiders, Centipedes, Millipedes                Insects, Spiders, Centipedes, Millipedes         A recently emerged cicada hangs on the fence at the Boyhood Home   A variety of insects and spiders reside in the Texas Hill Country. Lyndon B. Johnson National Historical Park is currently seeking funding and partners for a comprehensive survey of insects inhabiting the park.
